            CERES-EBAF and GISTEMP4 datasets are available from NASA (CERES-EBAF: https://asdc.larc.nasa.gov/data/CERES/EBAF/TOA_Edition4.2/; GISTEMP4: https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/). ERA5 is available from ECMWF (https://www.ecmwf.int/en/forecasts/dataset/ecmwf-reanalysis-v5). ERSSTv5 and GPCP are available from NOAA (ERSSTv5: https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/products/extended-reconstructed-sst; GPCP: https://psl.noaa.gov/data/gridded/data.gpcp.html). HadCRUT5 is available from the UK Met Office (https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/hadobs/hadcrut5/). CMIP6 model outputs are available through the Earth System Grid Federation (https://esgf-node.ipsl.upmc.fr/search/cmip6-ipsl/). The archives of CMIP6 and observational data, processed through regridding and area-averaging for plotting, are available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18132060 (ref. 51).
          Code availability

            The archiving of Python code used in this study is available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18132060 (ref. 51).
